        <h1>Support</h1>
<h1>About ParaOps</h1>
<p>ParaOps is a tactical airdrop planning tool built for pilots, loadmasters, jumpmasters, and drop zone support teams. It calculates computed air release points (CARPs) for both cargo and personnel operations, overlaid on an interactive map.</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Cargo Drops</strong> &mdash; SLP, CDS, PLF, and LE with full ballistic calculations including forward throw, wind drift, rate of fall, and safe DZ time.</li>
    <li><strong>Personnel Drops</strong> &mdash; MFF (HALO/HAHO/Combo) and HAPO with freefall drift, canopy drift, HARZ ring computation, and straddle time analysis.</li>
    <li><strong>Drop Zone Management</strong> &mdash; Define rectangular or circular DZs with PI coordinates, dimensions, run-in direction, and auto-fetched elevation and magnetic variation.</li>
    <li><strong>Wind Vectoriser</strong> &mdash; Enter wind layers at altitude to compute HIBAL and LOBAL ballistic winds in true or magnetic.</li>
    <li><strong>Weather</strong> &mdash; GFS forecast data from NOAA NOMADS for wind, temperature, and pressure at your DZ location.</li>
    <li><strong>Release Point</strong> &mdash; Automated CARP with radial, distance, run-in heading, ground speed, and escape planning. Jumpmaster RP override supported.</li>
    <li><strong>Reports &amp; Export</strong> &mdash; PDF CARP reports with satellite imagery, terrain profiles, and wind data. KML export for OzRunways, ForeFlight, or Google Earth. Shareable <code>.paradrop</code> files.</li>
    <li><strong>Logbook</strong> &mdash; Log missions with multi-leg flight times, aircraft callsign, drop events, and GPS trail recording.</li>
    <li><strong>Terrain Analysis</strong> &mdash; Elevation data along the run-in track with terrain profile visualisation.</li>
    <li><strong>Map Tools</strong> &mdash; Coordinate grid overlay, terrain shading, run-in visualisation with turning point and safe distance markers.</li>
</ul>

