        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3 style="color:#ccc; font-size:15px; margin-top:16px; margin-bottom:6px;">What devices does ParaOps support?</h3>
        <p>ParaOps is built for iPad running iOS 17 or later.</p>

        <h3 style="color:#ccc; font-size:15px; margin-top:16px; margin-bottom:6px;">Does the app require an internet connection?</h3>
        <p>An internet connection is needed to fetch weather data, terrain elevation, and magnetic variation. All other features work offline once data has been retrieved.</p>

        <h3 style="color:#ccc; font-size:15px; margin-top:16px; margin-bottom:6px;">Where is my data stored?</h3>
        <p>All data is stored locally on your device. ParaOps does not transmit personal data to external servers.</p>

        <h3 style="color:#ccc; font-size:15px; margin-top:16px; margin-bottom:6px;">How do I share a drop configuration?</h3>
        <p>Use the export feature to generate a <code>.paradrop</code> file, which can be shared with other ParaOps users via AirDrop, email, or any file sharing method.</p>

